cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this artifact, please cite it as below."
title: "bear-Schmidt: reproducible BEAR cyber-substrate demos (A through F)"
abstract: >
  Six reproducible demonstrations that exercise the substrate-level
  machinery of the BEAR (Behavioral Evolution And Retrieval) framework on
  cyber telemetry: (A) typed-gene schema, must-have reinjection, and
  per-must-have compliance telemetry C_m(t) on a closed-form-fitness
  pilot; (B) BEAR-MiniCAGE bridge with NIST/OpenC2-grounded compliance
  predicates against the Meander red agent on CAGE Challenge 2;
  (C) two-strategy co-evolution kernel with corrected invasion-fitness
  readout in single-defender and paired-defender variants;
  (D) BEAR-advantage demo with per-defender Corpus and Retriever and
  LLM-blended gene text at reproduction events, replicating the
  qualitative form of a previously reported heritability result on a
  cyber substrate; (E) generalization to CAGE Challenge 4 with five
  zone defenders, four pre-registered conditions, and audit-log-derived
  per-zone fitness; (F) decision-engine ablation in which a small
  local LLM (gemma-4-E2B-it served by vLLM) picks each per-tick action
  from gene-text directives, demonstrating that the substrate's
  monotone compliance scaling under reinjection rate rho is not an
  artifact of the rule-based decision engine used in Demos B and C.
